   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1812</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#411</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-411.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P(n)]]></fr:tex> be the proposition that for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s,t\in  A]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\mathrel {R^{\circ  n}}t]]></fr:tex> if and only if there exists a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">path</fr:link> of length <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> with source <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> and target <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>We shall prove <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> by induction.</fr:p>
 <fr:ol><fr:li>In the base case, we must prove <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P{\mathopen {}\left (0\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>: this states for for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s,t\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s=t]]></fr:tex> if and only if there exists a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">path</fr:link> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> of length <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex>. This holds by definition of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">paths</fr:link>, considering the unary tuple.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>In the inductive step, we may assume <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to prove <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P{\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s,t\in  A]]></fr:tex> we must show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s \mathrel {R^{\circ {\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}}}} t]]></fr:tex> if and only if there exists a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">path</fr:link> of length <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>. By definition, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s \mathrel {R^{\circ {\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}}}} t]]></fr:tex> if and only if there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s']]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\mathrel {R}s']]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s'\mathrel {R^{\circ  n}} t]]></fr:tex>. By our inductive hypothesis <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P{\mathopen {}\left (0\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> applied to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s',t]]></fr:tex>, the latter holds if and only if there exists a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">path</fr:link> of length <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s']]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>. As we can extend such a path by the link <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\mathrel {R}s']]></fr:tex>, we are done.</fr:li></fr:ol>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
