href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">endo-relations</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Observation</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>In the case of an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">endo-relation</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JH.xml"
addr="jms-00JH"
title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *}]]></fr:tex> can be computed using a finite union rather over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m \leq  n]]></fr:tex> rather than an infinite union over all of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>; in particular, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k \leq  n} R^{\circ  k}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
