xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1826</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00JN</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00JN.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph">Adjacency <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IS.xml"
addr="jms-00IS"
title="Matrix over a semiring">matrix</fr:link> of a finite <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JC.xml"
addr="jms-00JC"
title="Directed graph">directed graph</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We have seen in <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00I6.xml"
addr="jms-00I6"
title="Lecture 13: relations and matrices">Lecture 13</fr:link> (<fr:ref
addr="jms-00IY"
href="jms-00IY.xml"
taxon="Definition" />) how to turn any relation <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> into a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IS.xml"
addr="jms-00IS"
title="Matrix over a semiring">matrix</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> over the boolean semiring. When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:em>edge relation</fr:em> in a graph with vertices in the finite set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we refer to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (n,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as the <fr:em><fr:strong>adjacency matrix</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1829</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00JV</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00JV.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="The adjacency matrix of the reflexive-transitive closure">The <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JN.xml"
addr="jms-00JN"
title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph">adjacency matrix</fr:link> of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JH.xml"
addr="jms-00JH"
title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Algorithm</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JN.xml"
addr="jms-00JN"
title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph">adjacency matrix</fr:link> of a  finite <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JC.xml"
addr="jms-00JC"
title="Directed graph">directed graph</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}},R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We will show that the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JN.xml"
addr="jms-00JN"
title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph">adjacency matrix</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M^*]]></fr:tex> of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JH.xml"
addr="jms-00JH"
title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *}]]></fr:tex> can be computed recursively using the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JS.xml"
addr="jms-00JS"
title="Adding matrices together">additive</fr:link> and <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IW.xml"
addr="jms-00IW"
title="Multiplication of matrices">multiplicative</fr:link> structure of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IS.xml"
addr="jms-00IS"
title="Matrix over a semiring">matrices</fr:link>. In particular, we can define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M^* = M_n]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex> is computed recursively as below:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \begin {aligned}    M_0 &= I^n\\    M_{k+1} &= I^n + {\mathopen {}\left (M\cdot  M_k\right )\mathclose {}}  \end {aligned} ]]></fr:tex><fr:p>Thus we have a recursive algorithm that can deicde whether there is a path between two elemetns in a finite <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JC.xml"
addr="jms-00JC"
title="Directed graph">directed graph</fr:link>: indeed, there is a path from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M^*_{s,t} =\mathsf {true}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1832</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#406</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-406.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We first unravel the first few <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>’s</html:span> to get a better understanding.</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}    M_1 &= I^n + M\cdot  M_0    \\    &= I^n+M\cdot  I^n    \\    &= I^n + M    \\    M_2 &= I^n + M\cdot  M_1    \\    &= I^n + M\cdot  (I^n + M)    \\    &= I^n + M\cdot  I^n + M\cdot  M    \\    &= I^n + M + M^2   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>By induction, we can extend the pattern above to a closed form for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we deduce that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k = \sum _{l\leq  k} M^l]]></fr:tex> by recalling from <fr:ref
addr="jms-00J3"
href="jms-00J3.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> that the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IT.xml"
addr="jms-00IT"
title="The identity matrix">identity matrix</fr:link> is the neutral element for <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IV.xml"
addr="jms-00IV"
title="Product of matrices">matrix multiplication</fr:link>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n =\sum _{k \leq  n}M^k]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Our goal is to show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}} R^{\circ  *}]]></fr:tex>; we have already seen in <fr:ref
addr="jms-00JR"
href="jms-00JR.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> and <fr:ref
addr="jms-00J2"
href="jms-00J2.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> that <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JO.xml"
addr="jms-00JO"
title="Pointwise addition of matrices">matrix addition</fr:link> corresponds to union of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00I7.xml"
addr="jms-00I7"
title="Relation">relations</fr:link> and <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IV.xml"
addr="jms-00IV"
title="Product of matrices">matrix multiplication</fr:link> corresponds to <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">relational composition</fr:link>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>By <fr:ref
addr="jms-00JU"
href="jms-00JU.xml"
taxon="Observation" /> (<fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JU.xml"
addr="jms-00JU"
title="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations">reflexive-transitive closure of <fr:em>finite</fr:em> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JF.xml"
addr="jms-00JF"
title="Path in a directed graph">endo-relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}]]></fr:tex>. Therefore:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ *} = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>By <fr:ref
addr="jms-00JR"
href="jms-00JR.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> (<fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JR.xml"
addr="jms-00JR"
title="Matrix addition and union of relations"><fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JO.xml"
addr="jms-00JO"
title="Pointwise addition of matrices">matrix addition</fr:link> and union of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00I7.xml"
addr="jms-00I7"
title="Relation">relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}   =   \sum _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}  ]]></fr:tex>

 By <fr:ref
addr="jms-00J2"
href="jms-00J2.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> (<fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00J2.xml"
addr="jms-00J2"
title="Matrix product is relational composition"><fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IV.xml"
addr="jms-00IV"
title="Product of matrices">matrix product</fr:link> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">relational composition</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \sum _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}  =   \sum _{k\leq  n} {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\right )\mathclose {}}^k   =   \sum _{k\leq  n} M^k   = M_n  ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
