title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>directed graph</fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (A,R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> consists of a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00I7.xml"
addr="jms-00I7"
title="Relation">binary relation</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to itself; such a relation from a set to itself is called an <fr:em><fr:strong>endo-relation</fr:strong></fr:em>. We will abbreviate <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of all endo-relations on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
